public interface Predicate<P>

This interface provides a predicate, i.e. a kind of function that implements a logical statement and, when it is invoked, determines whether specified objects fulfill the statement. Predicates are highly related to functions. Like functions, predicates provide a set of invoke methods that can be used to evaluate the predicate. For providing predicates with and without parameters, this class contains invoke methods with zero, one and two arguments and with a typed list of arguments.
